summary:
SNEAK PEEK: Take A Look Inside The Nice & Accurate Good Omens TV Companion

  

The US Amazon listing of Good Omens tie-in title...
caption:
SNEAK PEEK: Take A Look Inside The Nice & Accurate Good Omens TV Companion

The US Amazon listing of Good Omens tie-in title The Nice And Accurate Good Omens TV Companion has been updated with a first glimpse of the inside of the eagerly anticipated behind-the-scenes guide. The much loved cult novel by Terry Prachett and Neil Gaiman has been adapted into a six-part series starring David Tennant as Crowley and Michael Sheen as Aziraphale which launches worldwide on Amazon Prime on May 31st.

Following the original novel’s chronological structure—from “the Beginning” to “End Times”—this official companion to the Good Omens television series, compiled by Matt Whyman, is a cornucopia of information about the show, its conception, and its creation. Offering deep and nuanced insight into Gaiman’s brilliantly reimagining of the Good Omens universe, The Nice and Accurate Good Omens TV Companion includes:

  • A foreword from Neil Gaiman
  • A profile of the director, Douglas McKinnon
  • Neil’s take on the adaptation process, in which he explains his goals, approach, and diversions from the original text
  • Interviews with the cast, including Michael Sheen, David Tennant, Nina Sosanya, Jon Hamm, Ned Dennehy, Josie Lawrence, Derek Jacobi, Nick Offerman, Frances McDormand, Miranda Richardson, Adria Arjona, and many others
  • More than 200 color photographs

And much more!

The must-have official companion guide to the Good Omens television series, Nice and Accurate TV Companion is a treasure trove of delights for fans of Good Omens, Neil Gaiman, and Terry Pratchett.

The book is due for release on 21st May and can be pre-ordered now via your local bookseller or through the links below:

UK: Pre-order The Nice and Accurate Good Omens TV Companion here

USA: Pre-order The Nice and Accurate Good Omens TV Companion here

Australia: Pre-order The Nice and Accurate Good Omens TV Companion here

summary: Have you written anything for Good Omens yet?
question: Have you written anything for Good Omens yet?
answer:
No, not yet, but I’ve got several ideas! Mostly crack-comedy stuff and parody. One kinda sweet, slightly dirty thing that I’ll probably never actually post. All based on the book more than the series so far. I almost want to wait for the Amazon series, though, before I post any Good Omens fan fiction but I may change my mind by then. May 31 is a long way off.

If anyone’s got any requests or suggestions, you can absolutely head over to @superwholock-viking-marquise and leave an ask!
